data.title: Day 3: Top Olympic shots from London
data.meta_description: All the action from London. Full Olympic coverage at chicagotribune.com/olympics
data.text:
Next ▶

USA's Candace Parker (15) is defended by Angola's Luisa Tomas (11) during their game at the Basketball Arena at the Olympic Park during the 2012 Summer Olympic Games in London, England. — Harry E. Walker, McClatchy-Tribune, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Nicaragua's Osmar Bravo Amador, left, reacts after he defeated Montenegro's Bosko Draskovic, right, in the men's Light Heavy (81kg) Round of 32 boxing match at ExCeL venue during the London 2012 Olympic Games. — Murad Sezer, Reuters, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Jake Dalton soars as he competes in the vault during the team men's gymnastic artistic team final at the North Greenwich Arena for the Summer Olympics in London. — Vernon Bryant, Dallas Morning News, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Matt Grevers of the United States and Nick Thoman of the United State celebrate after Grevers won the gold and Thoman took silver in the final of the Men's 100m Backstroke on Day 3 of the London 2012 Olympic Games. — Clive Rose, Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

China's team celebrates after taking the gold medal in the men's gymnastics team final at the London 2012 Olympic Games. China won the gold four years ago in Beijing. — Dylan Martinez, Reuters, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Danell Leyva of the U.S. falls from the pommel horse during the men's gymnastics team final in London — Dylan Martinez, Reuters, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

U.S. gymnast Jonathan Horton competes on the rings during the men's team final of the artistic gymnastics event of the London Olympic Games. — Thomas Coex, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

A Lam Shin of Korea crys after losing to Britta Heidemann of Germany in the Women's Epee Individual Fencing Semifinals on Day 3 of the London 2012 Olympic Games. — Hannah Johnston, Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

France's Dumerc jumps into the arms of teammate Yacoubou as they celebrate victory against Australia after their women's preliminary round Group B basketball match during the London 2012 Olympic Games. — Mike Segar, Reuters, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

A fleet of Laser class dinghies sails during the second race at the London 2012 Olympic Games in Weymouth and Portland, southern England. — Pascal Lauener, Reuters, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Britain's Tom Daley wraps a towel around his eyes in between dives in the men's synchronized 10m platform final at the Aquatics Centre. — Toby Melville, Reuters, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Russia's Iilya Zakharov and Victor Minibaev compete in the men's synchronized 10m platform final diving event at the Olympic Park in London. — Christophe Simon, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Vittoria Panizzon of Italy stumbles on Borough Pennyz in the Individual Eventing Cross Country Equestrian on Day 3 of the London 2012 Olympic Games at Greenwich Park. — Mike Hewitt, Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Automne Pavia of France celebrates her bronze medal B over Hedvig Karakas of Hungary during the Women's -57 kg Judo on Day 3 of the London 2012 Olympic Games. — Julian Finney, Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Austria's Werner Schlager serves to China's Wang Hao in the table tennis men's singles round match at the Excel centre in London. — Saeed Khan, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Peter Hellenbrand of The Netherlands competes in the 10m Air Rifle men final at the Royal Artillery Barracks in London — Marwan Naamani, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Britain's leftback Ewa Palies, left, vies with Russia's rightwing Olga Chernoivanenko during the women's preliminaries Group A handball match of Great Britain vs. Russia at the Copper Box hall in London. — Javier Soriano, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

William Coleman of the U.S. rides Twizzel past spectators as he competes in the Cross Country phase of the Eventing competition of the 2012 London Olympics at the Equestrian venue in Greenwich Park. — Adrian Dennis, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

U.S. swimmer Michael Phelps takes a third in the men's 200m butterfly heat swimming event at the London 2012 Olympic Games. — Christophe Simon, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Michael Phelps of the U.S. stretches before his men's 200m butterfly heat at the London 2012 Olympic Games at the Aquatics Centre. — Tim Wimborne, Reuters, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Japan's Yoshiaki Oiwa falls off his horse as he competes in the Cross Country phase of the Eventing competition at the Equestrian venue in Greenwich Park, London. — John MacDougall, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Italy's Federica Pellegrini, left, kisses Missy Franklin of the U.S. after finishing first in heat 3 of the women's 200m freestyle heats during the London 2012 Olympic Games at the Aquatics Centre. Franklin came in second. — Tim Wimborne, Reuters, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Julio Cesar Salamanca Pineda (ESA) snatch lifts 110 kg in the Men's 62kg weightlifting during the 2012 London Olympic Games at ExCeL - South Arena 3. — Matt Kryger, USA TODAY, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Rowing practice takes place on Day 3 of the London 2012 Olympic Games at Eton Dorney in Windsor, England. — Ezra Shaw, Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

U.S. swimmer Allison Schmitt competes in the women's 200m freestyle heats swimming event at the London 2012 Olympic Games. — Francois Xavier Marit, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

India's Devi Bombayia Laisharm competes during the women's individual event between India and Greece at Lord's Cricket Ground on in London. India defeated Greece. — Jewel Samad, AFP/Getty Images, July 30, 2012

◀ Previous Next ▶

Czech Republic's Ilona Burgrova and Jana Vesela fight for the ball with Turkey's Kuanitra Holingsvorth and Bahar Caglar during the women's preliminary round Group A basketball match. — Mike Segar, Reuters, July 30, 2012
